record.text: I believe we need to ramp up the Democratic campaign and fundraising apparatus to instead build democratic media if we ever want to have a chance of winning.

We need a new system for purchasing news subscriptions, no one wants to pay for 20 media outlets with 20 passwords. Someone needs to figure out how we can pay one subscription for multiple good media sources or pay a very small amount for each thing we read.

The media saw Trump tells massive lies about every issue and decided to stick that information in obscure fact-checks no one saw. Trump’s lies were one of the biggest stories of the election and the media chose to ignore it and leave voters misinformed.
Every Republican and Joe Manchin, but your average voter didn’t know that.
I also think a lot of people were mad that the child tax credit and other pandemic supports ended. They briefly had high disposable incomes and they it disappeared without explanation.

…fight against unpopular Trump/Vance/Project2025 Administration policies like climate crisis acceleration. There are no guardrails on Trump with possible exception of public opinion. Democrats need to be the public face of opposition as Trump pushes unpopular radical policies.
You can make that same argument for any minority group, but we choose to draw the line on what political rhetoric is acceptable.
It seems like a real strategic blunder in hindsight to try to out border control Trump instead of informing voters that immigrants have a lower crime rate and help the economy.

This seems like strong evidence that the deciding factor in this election was social media disinformation with an assist from mainstream media that was almost entirely horserace coverage and completely failed to inform voters.

Legally speaking would Trump be within his current powers as outlined by the SCOTUS to put out a hit on someone obstructing his agenda and pardon the killer? I hope the answer is no, but I don’t think it is.

I really don’t understand Harris’s decision to downplay climate change. It seems like that would have been a sure fire way to engage younger voters. It would help if she had a more effective bench of supporters to push those messages though.
True, Biden was world class bad at promoting his own successes and everyone involved should be banned from D politics, but progressives really dropped the ball too. They should have had his back.
It was such an own goal for the left to pressure Biden to enact progressive policies and then give him zero credit when he did it.
And what effect did Elon Musk have? He had both the ability to manipulate Twitter algorithms and access to the analytics.
I think it is social media. No one seems to be talking about that as a cause.
Has anyone broken out polling by main news source? My feeling all along is that social media is driving a lot of the shift in voting.
Voters were entirely uninformed and the media was too obsessed with polls to care.
